# Rule 6: Operations & Recovery

**Version:** 1.0 (NEW - Consolidates operational concerns)  
**Date:** December 6, 2025  
**Status:** ACTIVE - MANDATORY COMPLIANCE

**Migration Note:** This is a NEW rule that consolidates:
- Position Reconciliation (from former Rule 7, Phase 11+)
- Real-Time P&L Monitoring (from former Rules 4 & 7)
- Position Aging Management (from former Rule 7, Phase 10+)
- Settlement Management (NEW)
- Disaster Recovery (NEW)
- Operational Monitoring (NEW)

---

## Overview

Rule 6 defines **continuous operational processes** that run alongside the trading pipeline. These processes ensure **position integrity**, **accurate P&L tracking**, **timely settlement**, and **system resilience**.

**Key Principle:** Operational processes are **non-blocking** to the trading pipeline but **critical** for institutional-grade operations.

